<P>
9,000 BIRDS FOUND DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 9,000 sparrows migrating from Europe and Africa have been found dead 
along Brazil's northern coastline, a Brazilian newspaper reported Sunday. 
Remains of plastic were found in the birds' stomachs, leading scientists to 
conclude that ocean pollution was a main cause of the sparrows' death, the 
newspaper said. 
</P>
