<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; RESIDENT NAMED TO DEFENSE DEPARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Moorpark man has been appointed deputy assistant secretary of defense, 
officials have announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Fred Frostic, 52, a retired Air Force colonel and former Rand Corp. analyst, 
took his Pentagon post two weeks ago.Reached this weekend, Frostic said he will 
work for the undersecretary for plans and requirements. In his post, he will 
review the effectiveness of weapons system purchase by the Department of 
Defense. 
</P>
<P>
 "In the post-Cold War world, there are different types of threats we must 
prepare for," Frostic said. "We will look to see that our force size and 
defense systems will meet those threats." 
</P>
<P>
 Frostic and his wife will rent out their Moorpark home while they live in 
Washington, he said. He will be one of 60 deputy assistants. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is an exciting opportunity for me," Frostic said. "So far, it's been a 
lot of fun." SCOTT HADLY 
