<P>
 Coffee Crops Hit Again: Frost struck farms in southern Minas Gerais, Brazil's 
biggest coffee-growing state, and growers said the effects were harsher than 
the freeze that hit the area two weeks ago.Coffee prices soared after the 
previous cold snap, called the worst frost there in more than a decade. Brazil 
is the largest coffee producer in the world, and any threat to its crop 
dramatically affects world coffee prices. An official at a coffee cooperative 
confirmed there had been heavy frost but said it was too early to make a 
specific estimate of damage. 
