<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; PANEL TO CONSIDER BUILDING ICE RINK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission will consider a proposal today to build an ice hockey 
rink at a downtown site. 
</P>
<P>
 The rink, which would serve both as a practice site for the Mighty Ducks 
hockey team and a community youth center, would be built on a three-acre parcel 
at the southwest corner of Lincoln Avenue and Clementine Street. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ducks now practice at the Glacial Garden Ice Arena in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is a joint venture involving the Walt Disney Co. and the city of 
Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposed facility would house two ice rinks -- one Olympic size and the 
other National Hockey League size. The facility would also include a retail pro 
shop, an amusement arcade and a restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 The public hearing at City Hall begins at 1:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The Planning Commission staff has recommended that the commission approve the 
project. MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
