ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; GRANT APPLICATION DEADLINE IS SEPT. 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Community service groups have until Sept. 1 to submit proposals for $50,000 in 
grants to be awarded by the city this year. All nonprofit groups that provide 
needed services to Mission Viejo residents are eligible for the grants, which 
are awarded quarterly by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Groups do not have to be based in Mission Viejo, but their programs must 
benefit a substantial number of city residents. 
</P>
<P>
 Funding also can be extended to special civic and cultural events. 
</P>
<P>
 Priority is given to organizations that provide services to the largest number 
of Mission Viejo residents and satisfy a social need that would otherwise go 
unfilled. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are reviewed by city staff, and the City Council decides how the 
grants are awarded. 
</P>
<P>
 Nonprofit groups interested in applying for the community service funds can 
pick up an application at City Hall, 26522 La Alameda. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, contact Virginia Chavez at the Parks and Community 
Services Department at (714) 348-2061.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
