<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESIDENCE DAMAGED IN FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A two-story house in Valencia sustained $300,000 in damage after a fire broke 
out on the second floor, county fire officials said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Sue Pearson, 54, was in her home in the 24500 block of Farrow Drive 
Saturday afternoon when she smelled smoke.The odor became stronger and she saw 
smoke outside her rear window. When she walked outside the house, she saw that 
smoke was coming from her roof, and called firefighters. 
</P>
<P>
 Five engine companies from the Los Angeles County Fire Department responded 
and brought the fire under control in about 30 minutes. Neither Pearson nor any 
firefighters were injured. 
</P>
<P>
 The roof of the house was destroyed and the second floor sustained major 
damage, fire officials said. Damage to the structure and its contents was 
estimated at $300,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the fire is still under investigation. 
</P>
