<P>
2 YOUTHS JAILED IN CAR THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two teen-agers were arrested on suspicion of car theft after a short pursuit 
in Lancaster on Sunday morning, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Harris, 18, and a 16-year-old were traveling in a stolen 1985 Cadillac 
near 10th Street East and Avenue I about 10:15 a.m. when sheriff's deputies 
attempted to stop them, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies chased the car for about two minutes, but called off the chase to 
avoid injury when the suspects sped into a residential neighborhood. The car 
was spotted several minutes later and the suspects were arrested, deputies 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies found no weapons, but recovered two screwdrivers and pawn slips from 
the car, which deputies say might have been used in burglaries. 
