workers, the company has annual revenues of $1.2 billion. Its numerous business 
lines are conducted through two major operating units: Crowley American 
Transport Inc., based in Jacksonville, Fla., and Crowley Marine Services Inc. 
of Seattle. Under Crowley's direction, the company pioneered bulk petroleum 
barge service on the Pacific Coast. In 1958 it performed the first commercial 
resupply of the Distant Early Warning Line installations in the Arctic. In San 
