<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; WHAT'S THE SECRET? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL PLASCHKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As expected, German forward Rudi Voeller announced after the game that he was 
retiring from the team. 
</P>
<P>
 A bit more surprising was the announcement from goalkeeper Bodo Illgner that 
he was also retiring. 
</P>
<P>
 An angry German Coach Vogts expected Illgner to keep the news a secret for 
now. 
</P>
<P>
 "He told me in the cabin (locker room) that he was retiring, but he was only 
going to tell me and not announce it," Vogts said. "Then I come out of the 
cabin and he has told the media. That tells me something about somebody's 
character." BILL PLASCHKE 
</P>
