</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DOWNEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bora Milutinovic would welcome being asked back as U.S. soccer coach, he said 
Sunday at the Sweden-Romania game at Palo Alto. 
</P>
<P>
 Asked if he would return, Milutinovic said: "I hope so. 
</P>
<P>
 "It depends on who is going to be the new president," he added, alluding to 
Alan Rothenberg's eventual successor as head of the U.S. federation. "I do not 
think there is going to be a problem, but first we must see what the president 
wishes. I would very much hope to continue the work that we have just begun." 
